A member of the class of piperidines that is piperidine substituted by ethyl and 2-methylbutyl groups at positions 1 and 3, respectively.

A derivatised tetrapeptide in which a parent tetrapeptide comprising glycine, L-serine, glycine and L-leucine residues coupled in sequence, has its terminal glycine residue  acetylated on nitrogen and its serine residue L-glycero-alpha-D-heptosylated on oxygen.
An alkene that is tricosane carrying 1 double bond (the position of the double bond is unspecified).
A synthetic tetrapeptide comprising glycine, L-serine, glycine and L-leucine residues coupled in sequence.
A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptopyranose.
A primary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of 4-aminobenzoic acid resulting from the protonation of the amino group.
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 4-aminobenzoic acid.

A derivatised tetrapeptide in which a parent tetrapeptide comprising glycine, L-serine, glycine and L-leucine residues coupled in sequence, has its terminal glycine residue acetylated on nitrogen and its serine residue D-glycero-alpha-D-heptosylated on oxygen.
A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of D-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptopyranose.
A retinoid anion that is the conjugate base of 4-hydroxy-all-trans-13,14-dihydroretinoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A retinoid that is all-trans-13,14-dihydroretinoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4.
An oxo dicarboxylic acid that is but-2-enedioic acid substituted by an amino group at position 2 and a 3-oxoprop-1-enyl group at position 3.
An octadecadienoic acid having two double bonds located at positions 5 and 8 (the 5Z,8Z-geoisomer).
A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a [3-(4-oxo-4H-chromen-2-yl)benzoyl]nitrilo group.
A member of the class of phosphoranes that is phosphorane in which all 5 hydrogen's are replaced by phenyl groups.
